    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL PAN, VIBRATION DAMPER, OIL
        PUMP, WATER PUMP, AND FRONT COVER - Installation - Oil Pick-Up Tube
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Pick-Up Tube</title>
        <figure id="f1200533" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3337.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Oil Pick-Up Tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Stud-Bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bracket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pick-Up Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flange</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-Ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the O-ring on the oil pick-up tube mounting flange. If necessary, use a small amount
                of RTV sealant to hold the O-ring in place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil pick-up tube at the front cover and main bearing stud bolt. Tighten the
                flange bolts finger tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust the bracket at the main bearing cap stud. Tighten the flange bolts to the standard
                torque value after alignment. Tighten the nut at the main bearing cap stud last.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
